30/01/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Montenegro is finalising preparations to apply for EU membership candidate status and will submit its application shortly, Montenegrin Deputy Prime Minister Gordana Djurovic said on Tuesday (January 29th). She added that Montenegro is working to align its legislation with EU standards and strengthen its administrative capacities. Administrative problems have often been cited as Montenegro's biggest challenge in the integration process. (RTCG, Mina - 29/01/08)
